{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Both of these "contracts" are often initiated under desperate circumstances or by ill informed people.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to the [Global Commission on Drug Policy](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Global_Commission_on_Drug_Policy), the war on drugs was a failure. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Most [drug users](http://theconversation.com/many-people-use-drugs-but-heres-why-most-dont-become-addicts-35504) can rely on supportive networks and loving families. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It may be very difficult to diagnose which individuals suffer from self-inflicted mental illness or trauma and which ones are taking drugs as a result of their condition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of this emotional harm is directly caused by erroneous negative perceptions of drug use like the ones being perpetrated here. Many people are unfairly vilified for responsibly using drugs, simply because they are illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Hallucinogens such as LSD and magic mushrooms have been used to create many great artworks. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The US government has [previously supported](https://www.ozy.com/flashback/when-the-government-said-marijuana-made-you-crazy/88232) the claim that marijuana use causes individuals to rape and murder others, or commit suicide. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Making it legal for companies to sell and market these drugs for recreational use without an understanding of the negative consequences that these substances cause is unethical. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Holland, [a channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCvRQKXtIGcK1yEnQ4Te8hWQ) exists just to raise awareness of drugs. It explains how and when to take them, and what to do when a friend is having an OD.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Alcohol](https://theconversation.com/alcohol-leads-to-more-violence-than-other-drugs-but-youd-never-know-from-the-headlines-72281) is responsible for more violence and harm than any other drug.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a [correlation](https://americanaddictioncenters.org/rehab-guide/addiction-and-violence) between drug use and \\(violent\\) crime.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Places that have decriminalised some or all drugs have not observed a long-term increase in consumption, and occasionally even a decrease has been observed. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar legal compound will act the same way as the original one.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Knowledge that a friend or relative is using drugs can cause significant psychological stress to a caring or sensitive individual.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegality over the last century has halted research on the many new psychoactive substances that have been discovered in that time \\(as well as traditional ones\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's already true in [most states \\(USA\\)](https://www.ghsa.org/state-laws/issues/drug%20impaired%20driving)"}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Affordable drugs will more likely lessen the negative impacts of drug use, as overall users would be less likely to abuse substances due to psychological distress caused by financial instability.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Information about the content of legalized drugs would be easier to find and accurate which would help people make informed and safer choice.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization might lead to increased consumption among children.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Psychedelics are often used for [one-off, recreational and spiritual](https://www.livescience.com/61902-psychedelic-drugs-change-personality.html) experiences. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has only permitted research which [supports their agenda](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/08/18/feds-limit-research-marijuana-medical-use/31547557/) of prohibition. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has lead to [high incarceration rates](https://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/jul/10/cory-booker/how-war-drugs-affected-incarceration-rates/) of otherwise inoffensive citizens. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Numerous events have an equal impact on moral judgments; This should not be the reason for the ban on drug use. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The increased tax revenue could enable increased government spending, which [results in more jobs](https://www.americanprogress.org/issues/economy/reports/2011/09/08/10257/government-spending-can-create-jobs-and-it-has/).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Opiates have a [rich history](https://www.history.com/topics/crime/history-of-heroin-morphine-and-opiates) of recreational use, with the Ancient Sumerians calling it "The Joy Plant".'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegal drug dealers typically require no age verification from their clients. Legal drugs would require ID to buy thus making them harder for teens to aquire. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Giving up" is preferable to endlessly pursuing an unobtainable goal.'}
